  "prompt": "Facebook: What is the revenue model of Facebook?",
  "response": "Facebook's (now Meta's) primary revenue model is based on digital advertising. Here are the key components:\n\n1. Targeted Advertising\n- Collects user data (demographics, interests, behaviors)\n- Allows advertisers to target specific audience segments\n- Offers precise ad targeting across Facebook, Instagram, and Messenger\n\n2. Ad Formats\n- News Feed ads\n- Story ads\n- Video ads\n- Carousel ads\n- Sponsored content\n- Display ads\n\n3. Advertising Platforms\n- Facebook Ads Manager\n- Instagram Ads\n- Audience Network (third-party apps and websites)\n\n4. Additional Revenue Streams\n- Virtual reality hardware (Oculus)\n- Marketplace transaction fees\n- WhatsApp Business API\n- Horizon Worlds (metaverse platform)\n\n5. Business Model Characteristics\n- Majority (97-98%) of revenue comes from advertising\n- Free platform for users\n- Monetizes user attention and data\n- Advanced algorithms for ad targeting\n- Large user base (2.9+ billion monthly active users)\n\nThe core strategy is leveraging user data to create highly targeted, personalized advertising experiences for businesses, generating substantial advertising revenue.",
